Without specifying a bottom constraint (and using `wrap_content` for the height), the `ScrollView` will size itself to be large enough that all of the content fits inside of it, but is clipped by the parent `ConstraintLayout`. If all the content fits, there&#39;s nothing to scroll (even though you can&#39;t see it all, since the parent is clipping it).

